title: Glmnet, XGBoost, and SVM Using tidymodels
review: A well-structured and documented tutorial on how to use the new [tidymodels](https://tidymodels.tidymodels.org/) framework on the House Prizes regression problem.

title: Breathe India: COVID-19 effect on Pollution
review: A detailed work studying the interaction between the big topics of COVID-19 and air pollution in past and recent data from India.

title: U.S. Commercial Flights Tracker Map
review: Stunning maps are accompanied by lots of other fantastic visuals in this outstanding Notebook by one of my favourite Kagglers. Tons of dataviz inspiration in this criminally underrated work.

title: Unbiased Look on Brazil Wildfires
review: A well-focused analysis on a globally important topic. Enriched by vivid maps, context info, and narration.

title: MNIST 2D t-SNE with Rapids
review: One of the first Notebooks on Kaggle demonstrating the game-changing speed up provided by Nvidia's GPU-magic tools. An exhibit as concise and powerful as the code itself.

title: How good does your chocolate taste?
review: A flavourful composition of layers of data wrangling and exploratory visuals; sprinkled with inspiration for modelling.

title: The 12 Different Types of Kagglers
review: A creative clustering analysis of the [1st Kaggle Survey](https://www.kaggle.com/kaggle/kaggle-survey-2017). Lots of inspiration for future surveys. What type of Kaggler are you?

title: Shifterator analysis on Animal Crossing reviews
review: A concise tutorial on the promising new [shifterator package](https://github.com/ryanjgallagher/shifterator) which provides a visual approach to interpretable NLP characterisations. Demonstrated using a timely (TidyTuesday) dataset of Animal Crossing reviews.

title: NYC Schools Race, Attendance Economy
review: A contribution to one Kaggle's excellent 'Data Science for Good' challenges, this Notebook explores high school characteristics and demographics with inventive and intricate visuals.

title: A deep learning of Deep Learning
review: A deep meta-look into the deep learning preferences of our deeply fascinating community. Narrated and illustrated based on data from the [2019 Kaggle Survey](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2019). It will be interesting to see how the numbers change in 2020 and beyond.

title: German Credit Analysis || A Risk Perspective
review: This work presents a thorough exploration of risky business in Germany. It deserves much credit for its well-organised structure and expertly designed visuals.

title: Kiva Loans EDA part 1 | Interactive Visualizations
review: A tightly focussed analysis of the 2018 *Data Science for Good* challenge for the [Kiva Crowdfunding platform](https://www.kaggle.com/kiva/data-science-for-good-kiva-crowdfunding). Innovative interactive plots engage the reader with the rich data.

title: Police Policy and the Use of Deadly Force
review: This work addresses the timely subject of police violence. A careful EDA of the associated dataset provides a great starting point for other Kagglers to become more involved in studying this important issue.

title: Zoomable Circle Packing via D3.js in IPython
review: A technical Notebook on beautiful interactive visuals which, like all of Anisotropic's contributions, is expertly designed and documented. Here's to hoping that this early Kaggle hero of mine will soon return from his sabbatical.

title: How good is Luka Doncic?
review: In the style of a data-packed sports article, this impressive Notebook showcases the equally impressive career achievements of a young basketball star. Great attention to narrative and visual details.

title: Chocolate Bar Ratings: Extensive EDA
review: A nuanced exploration of chocolate ratings with great visuals and thoughtful narration. A dash of modelling completes the comprehensive analysis.

title: How big is French Industry? [Data Visualization]
review: This work presents a thorough study of the French workforce and wage structure using detailed maps and summary graphs.

title: Food Feed Facts
review: First-rate findings, featuring focussed & fine-tuned figures. Great emphasis on detailed data quality checks.

title: Kiva in 2 minutes Animated Story
review: This well-crafted combination of static, interactive, and animated map visuals provides great inspiration for spatial projects. Also note the focus on Data Science for Good.

title: A look back at your Kaggle journey!
review: With Kaggle approaching fast the magic number of 5 million sign-ups, this compact Notebook demonstrates how to recount your (or anyone's) Kaggle journey using the [Meta Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/kaggle/meta-kaggle) dataset. Includes inspiration for further analysis.

title: COVID19 statistical analysis in Germany
review: A well-documented and structured analysis of the early COVID-19 data for Germany. Presents a comprehensive analysis of geo-spatial features, taking into account state-level and county-level population densities.

title: Quantify the Madness, a study of competitiveness
review: A striking master class in designing a captivating study with great narrative flow and well-thought-out visuals. Analyses the subject of competitiveness in basketball based on [March Madness data](https://www.kaggle.com/c/march-madness-analytics-2020/).

title: Australia on fire - Animation
review: A short and sweet Notebook that builds an impressive interactive plotly visualisation showing the evolution of wildfires in Australia in the Summer of 2019.

title: RoBERTa meets TPUs
review: On the example of the recent [Tweet Sentiment Competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/tweet-sentiment-extraction), this well-organised Notebook provides a patient and detailed introduction to cutting-edge NLP with RoBERTa and PytorchLightning. Contains lots of resources plus TPU integration.

title: How was the growth of Kaggle? Insightful Approach
review: We start with a fitting study that presents a detailed analysis of the growth of our community in the different categories through various methods. Last run when there were 3.5 million sign-ups, it's well worth updating for this new, exciting milestone.

title: Airlines Route Tracker
review: Beautiful maps of airline frequencies and routes from one of Kaggle's most prolific Notebook authors. Great attention to detail and exemplary engagement with comments from the community.

title: How Long It Takes to Win 1st on Kaggle
review: A nifty, brief Notebook studying how long after joining Kaggle it took past competition winners to achieve their 1st victory. Last ran 3 years ago, it would be interesting to see whether the trend of faster wins has continued in recent years.

title: AfricAI
review: A reflection on AI in Africa based on the [2018 Kaggle survey](https://www.kaggle.com/kaggle/kaggle-survey-2018). Great narrative style that intersperses insights with quotes from researchers and also with personal annecdotes.

title: Making perfect "Chai" and other tales :)
review: The male winner of the competition delivers an excellently illustrated and structured exploration of a wide range of CTDS features. Impressive storytelling skills meet a talent for visual guides.
notes: This week's episode is a special edition on the recently finished [Chai Time Data Science (CTDS) show Notebooks competition](https://www.kaggle.com/rohanrao/chai-time-data-science/discussion/168310). All three featured Notebooks will be outstanding contributions to this contest.

title: Does Twitter Chirp Chai?
review: The female winner of the competition presents a well-focussed analysis of the social media aspect of the CTDS interviews. Engaging and humourous narration makes this Notebook a joy to read.
notes: This week's episode is a special edition on the recently finished [Chai Time Data Science (CTDS) show Notebooks competition](https://www.kaggle.com/rohanrao/chai-time-data-science/discussion/168310). All three featured Notebooks will be outstanding contributions to this contest.

title: CTDS - Subtitles exploration
review: A fresh analysis of speaking patterns and conversation flow based on the subtitle transcripts of each episode. Also note the question clustering and answer summarisation insights.
notes: This week's episode is a special edition on the recently finished [Chai Time Data Science (CTDS) show Notebooks competition](https://www.kaggle.com/rohanrao/chai-time-data-science/discussion/168310). All three featured Notebooks will be outstanding contributions to this contest.

title: Visual journey through world development 1985-2015

title: Santander: EDA + features
review: A great example for an end-to-end framework to model anonymised & sparse tabular data. The next Santander competition is never far away ;-)

title: What's this? Chai and DataScience?
review: Another excellent analysis of CTDS show data (see Vol. 12), where great storytelling & structure are interspersed by entertaining visuals.

title: Wildfire Exploratory Analysis
review: A detailed analysis of extensive US wildfire data with great visuals. Note in particular the clever use of tabs to structure sections in a compact yet comprehensive way.

title: Recommendation engine with networkx
review: Step-by-step guide to building a Netflix recommendation engine; resulting in insightful and visually pleasing output graphs.

title: Alzheimer MRI Model + TensorFlow 2.3 Data Loading
review: End-to-end tutorial for classifying dementia in MRI images. Demonstrates new features in TF 2.3 and Keras.

title: Recommending Music Artists with Boltzmann Machines
review: A detailed introduction to Restricted Boltzmann Machines, with helpful illustrations and equations, on the example of music recommendations. The code and concepts are being explained with great educational skills.

title: How long does it take to be GM
review: A compact [Meta Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/kaggle/meta-kaggle) analysis of how much time it takes Kagglers to reach the ranks of Competitions Expert, Master, or Grandmaster. Clever idea; and lots of possibilities to build on it for further exploration.

title: Best part of the cake, worst part of Hockey: Icing
review: From the magnificent title pun to the fun little sketches; this Notebook is a joy to read. I learned much more about ice hockey oddities than I had expected.

title: Bank Marketing Analysis
review: A detailed end-to-end analysis of a marketing-based binary classification problem. Well structured and documented.

title: Video games sales analysis and visualization
review: Fun and engaging narration provides the scaffolding for gaming insights on genres and regional levels.

title: Candy Production: Time Series Analysis
review: A sweet selection of classical time series analysis methods. Interactive visuals provide additional eye candy.

title: Maps of NYC Airbnbs with Python

title: Trending YouTube Video Metadata Analysis
review: A comprehensive EDA with a focus on which factors drive the number of views for videos trending on Youtube. Also note the emphasis on data quality assessments.

title: Building Resnet34 from scratch using PyTorch
review: A step-by-step Pytorch blueprint for assembling a ResNet architecture from basic components. Well structured and clearly explained.

title: Alone in the woods: Using Theil's U for survival
review: An exploratory work featuring strong narrative elements alongside an entropy approach to a classification problem with a set of categorical features.

title: Contradictory Watson: Concise Keras XLM-R on TPU
review: Get quickly started in the [NLP Contradiction Competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/contradictory-my-dear-watson/) with XLM-Roberta and TPU through Tensorflow. Featuring Huggingface tokenizers.

title: Mechanisms of Action: What Do We Have Here?
review: A comprehensive and well-structured EDA that provides a big-picture overview of the dataset, while also highlighting and commenting on important individual features.

notes: This week's episode is a special issue on the recently launched [Mechanisms of Action competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/lish-moa/).

review: Demonstrating a [new package](https://github.com/tmabraham/UPIT), built on the fastai framework, to implement CycleGANs in a concise and elegant way.

review: A well-designed tour of a criminal justice dataset; complete with customised visuals and a carefully structured narrative. All grey-haired dogs approve.

title: A tour of the oil industry
review: An impressive deep-dive into oil industry data. Note the comprehensive documentation and interpretation that accompanies the great seaborn visuals.

title: Tutorial on reading large datasets
review: An impressively clean and accessible primer on Python tools to read, and formats to store, large datasets. Brief and to the point; featuring Pandas, Dask, Datable, and Rapids cudf.

review: History has its eyes on this R Keras tutorial showcasing the ten NLP commandments to predict the non-stop lyrics of the musical Hamilton. And we don't even have to wait for it.

review: This EDA on the Melbourne housing market presents a number of interesting dataviz approaches via plotly. Also note the consistent use of explanations that interpret the visuals.

title: Fun with Meteorites Landings w/ Maps
review: An extensive exploration of meteorites found on earth. Note the use of interactive leaflet maps to explore the global distributions of impact sites and meteorite characteristics.

title: Animation - GAN Latent Walk
review: A great and concise example for how to visualise transitions between generative images. Build your own gifs using a Tensorflow GAN.

title: Divorce Prediction with RF
review: This Notebook shows an interesting structure: after building a model, it takes a step back and provides extensive domain context in which the model results are then interpreted.

title: Time Series Analysis, Forecast with Visualization
review: A well-structured and documented showcase of using popular time-series methods to predict US border crossings. Note the clean visuals that focus on communicating specific insights.

title: kaggle discussions: Busiest time of the day?
review: A brief and compact Notebook providing a glimpse into the daily discussion patterns of the Kaggle community. When are we most active, and where in the world could we live?

title: Where to invest to combat air pollution in India?
review: With its engaging narration, detailed interpretations, and wide variety of visuals and illustrations, this Notebook is a master class in presenting a comprehensive analysis.

title: The math of the neuron with animation
review: This Notebook provides a detailed mathematical review of neural network fundamentals like activations and back propagation. It includes an animated example of a simple 2d classification problem.

title: Hugging Face Transformers - Get started !
review: A great starter notebook on NLP transformer models by the huggingface team. Note the focus on comprehensive explanations and clean, well annotated code.

title: Image Recognition from Scratch! #1
review: In another close look into neural network building blocks, this well-structured work explains convolutional image tools such as different kernel filter methods and edge detectors.

title: moa_all_rapids
review: This work implements fast modelling for the ongoing [MoA competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/lish-moa) entirely within the impressive Rapids GPU-powered framework. Great template for rapid iterations.

title: Starter Code : EDA and LGBM Baseline
review: A clean end-to-end Notebook like one hopes to find when joining a competition: featuring a variety of visualisation techniques alongside a tunable starter model.

title: Battle of the Boosting Algos: LGB, XGB, Catboost
review: A benchmarking Notebook on the performance of the most popular tree boosters for different classification and prediction challenges. Worth the occasional rerun.

title: [Plotly] Avatar : The Last Airbender Analysis
review: A visual exploration of the beloved Nickelodeon show Avatar. Note the detailed interpretations of insights within the context of the show's narrative. Flameo, hotman!

title: The Convolutional Classifier
review: The opening Notebook in Kaggle's new [Computer Vision course](https://www.kaggle.com/learn/computer-vision) starts the lessons with hands-on transfer learning on CNNs and Tensorflow/Keras. Also check out the rest of the course.

title: Geospatial Feature Engineering and Visualization
review: This is a well-documented guide on data augmentation and feature design for a housing dataset. Comes with a few interesting ideas for geospatial plots.

title: Tabular XGboost GPU + FFT GPU + Cuml = FAST
review: With the GPU-powered Rapids framework now natively available on Kaggle, this notebook presents a clean and concise end-to-end pipeline for the new [rainforest audio competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/rfcx-species-audio-detection) in trademark Giba style.

title: Complete Visualization and Analysis of 2020Debates
review: An exploration and text analysis of the 2020 presidential debates. Note the consistent use of detailed narration to guide the reader through the notebook.

title: Education level affects data analysis?

title: How unique are you on Kaggle? Get your score here!

review: An exeptionally well organised guide to using the Xception architecture for building a model in the soon to be concluded [Leaf Disease competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/cassava-leaf-disease-classification). The clean code really stands out.

title: Pokemon Battles
review: Another fantastic end-to-end analysis by one of Kaggle's most prolific Notebook authors. Note in particular the radar charts, consistent narrative flow, and how every question in the comments is answered in detail.

title: Keras Neural Network - A hitchhiker's guide to NN
review: Don't panic when seeing [Titanic data](https://www.kaggle.com/c/titanic) - use this guide with clean visuals, thoughtful narration, and clear structure to get you started. Now you'll always know where your towel is.

title: Explore Global Terrorism using Highcharter
review: This compact work presents clean and gorgeous visuals that explore the temporal and geospatial features of terror attacks in a dashboard-like style. Note the interactivity.

title: Discussion Hotness Plots
review: A detailed visual inspection of the inner workings of Kaggle's Discussion Hotness ranking from when it failed to be properly updated in the summer of 2020. Meta and insightful.

title: High or low-quality question on StackOverflow?
review: A well-designed exploratory analysis of a Stack Overflow questions dataset. Note how the clean visuals have a consistent style and are accompanied by focussed interpretation and narration.

title: Rethinking CV Strategy with Visualizations
review: This work lays out a clever cross validation strategy using stratification on groups that are derived from an unsupervised clustering of input images. Nice idea for noisy labels.

title: Time Series Forecasting: Building Intuition
review: A visual dive into time series forecasting. Uses toy data to examine the impact of model parameters and finding a good validation split. The narration features interesting menu metaphors.

title: Games - Strategy ideas from EDA
review: An exploration of historical March Madness data, which remains relevant for this year's competition. Featuring a clean structure, and a number of pretty interesting and unique visualisation ideas.

title: Joyful Analysis of death causes
review: This work showcases detailed narration and interpretation while analysing the grim dataset of celebrity deaths. The author manages well to explain her thought processes and decisions.

title: AMA With a Data Scientist
review: This notebook presents an entertaining journey through past Kaggle survey data. Written in an interview style, it touches on many of the key aspects of Data Science practitioners and their jobs.

title: ML and Kaggle : A Hardware lottery ?
review: A very well written and researched article on the proliferation of computing hardware requirements in ML research and Kaggle competitions. Enriched with Kaggle survey data and expertly structured.

title: Time Series Transformations
review: Originally written for last year's [M5 competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/m5-forecasting-accuracy), this work is a useful primer on transformations for time series problems in general. Detailed descriptions accompany clean code.

title: Competitiveness, and expertise in Tennis
review: A comprehensive and well annotated analysis of various factors that influence the winning probability in professional tennis tournaments, such as match duration or playing surface.

title: What's going on in Ecuador? - splash of Plotly
review: This work is studying global warming trends in cities around the world, using a number of expertly designed plot layouts. While you're there, also check out the sister Notebook on Bokeh.

title: The Path to Tidier Data
review: On the example of the popular [World University Ranking dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/mylesoneill/world-university-rankings/) this Notebook demonstrates several data cleaning and reshaping techniques that remain ever relevant.

title: Cassava Leaf Disease VIT TPU Training
review: When a competition ends, the winner's solutions often receive far less attention than they deserve. This work shows (one of) the winning model(s) from [Cassava](https://www.kaggle.com/c/cassava-leaf-disease-classification); with clean code plus detailed [write-up](https://www.kaggle.com/c/cassava-leaf-disease-classification/discussion/221957).

title: RANZCR 1st Place Soluiton Cls Model (small ver.)
review: Another underrated 1st place competition notebook: this well-structured work demonstrates a part of the 2-stage segmentation plus classification approach that won the recent [RANZCR imaging challenge](https://www.kaggle.com/c/ranzcr-clip-catheter-line-classification).

title: Getting Started with Biopython
review: A narrated introduction to using the [Biopython library](https://biopython.org/) on a [genome dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/mylesoneill/drosophila-melanogaster-genome). Note the way in which the code is enriched with detailed explanations and interpretations.

title: EDA of Murders in India
review: This Notebook presents a visual exploration of a grim topic. A variety of charts are accompanied by their interpretations by the author, which help the reader to access the displayed information.

title: Space Missions & Tech Race | Space Theme plots
review: This compact work presents a number of visuals with interesting dark-theme design on the subject of space missions and launches.

title: Titanic: Machine Learning from Disaster - EDA
review: The good old Titanic dataset is being meticulously explored here, with extensive interpretation provided alongside multiple eye-catching and well-designed visualisation layouts.

title: The World Belongs to Those Who Read
review: An exploratory analysis of best-selling books that shines when it comes to storytelling and interpretation. Images of relevant book covers provide nice visual elements.

title: What gets you a home loan in Washington?
review: This Notebook features detailed narration in its step-by-step analysis of a [mortgage dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/miker400/washington-state-home-mortgage-hdma2016); thereby achieving much higher engagement with the reader than stand-alone visuals could provide.

title: EDA of a Netflix dataset with Plotly in R
review: An exploratory analysis of [Netflix content](https://www.kaggle.com/shivamb/netflix-shows) featuring data cleaning, nicely integrated interactive tables, and aesthetically pleasing visuals which also all have interactivity via the plotly library.

title: Amazon Bestselling Books EDA and Price Prediction
review: This well-structured work explores the [dataset of best-selling Amazon books](https://www.kaggle.com/sootersaalu/amazon-top-50-bestselling-books-2009-2019) in a clean and systematic way. The EDA is accompanied by a price prediction model.

title: Earthquakes And Tectonic Plates: Seismic Analysis
review: A clean and well narrated exploration of earthquake data. Custom infographics effectively explain the data features and conclusion. Interactive geospatial maps highlight the role of tectonic plates.

title: EDA, Hypothesis Testing, MLR | Stats Report Style
review: This impressive debut Notebook presents multiple great plot layouts with extensive interpretation. Statistical tests, a baseline model, and a discussion section with references are other strong features.

title: Beware of trolls
review: An expertly crafted analysis of troll tweets; featuring a range of diverse visuals, a concise setup, and careful notes and interpretations. Note in particular the heatmap and annotated time series.

title: Reddit Vaccine Myths EDA and Text Analysis
review: An extensive exploration of vaccine-related discussions on reddit, featuring great visuals and table styling. Note the sentiment analysis of a topic that really shouldn't be that controversial.

title: Kiva-Detailed Analysis using Highcharter & Leaflet
review: This work presents a diverse range of interactive visualisations to study global crowdfunding efforts to alleviate poverty. The highcharter time series and the leaflet maps are particularly powerful.

title: 2. Encourage Diversity, Reduce Bias - CoLA
review: An exceptionally well structured analysis of gender bias in job postings; as part of a multi-notebook series. The clean visuals blend nicely into the text, and the narration is next level.

title: Formula 1 70th Anniversary
review: This exploratory Notebook is racing ahead with creative visuals, distinctive styling, and well-crafted animations all about the 2020 Formula 1 season.

title: Dive into dplyr (tutorial #1)
review: A well-structured guide to R dplyr functionality showcased on the [palmer penguin dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/parulpandey/palmer-archipelago-antarctica-penguin-data). Does a great job in elucidating the tidyverse approach and philosophy.

title: EfficientDet meets Pytorch Lightning
review: A very extensive introduction to object detection with Pytorch with detailed narration. Numerous graphs, examples, and equations punctuate the text and illustrate the concepts.

title: COVID-19 World Vaccination Progress
review: A well organised Notebook which demonstrates how readability is drastically improved through section headers, compact code, and nuggets of interpretation and narration that accompany visuals.

title: Forecast with N-BEATS || Interpretable model
review: This work presents a detailed introduction on a neural network time series forecasting method, complete with applied examples. Note the clean structure and helpful visuals.

title: World Happiness Index Report
review: This Notebook assembles a large set of diverse visualisations to study happiness indices in a global context; in particular the various heatmaps, panel layouts, and density plots.

title: Identifying Bias in AI
review: This Notebook constitutes a key lessons in Kaggle's new [Intro to AI Ethics course](https://www.kaggle.com/learn/intro-to-ai-ethics). Understanding sources of bias is crucial as ML products become more and more powerful.

title: Air Pollution 101
review: A detailed exploration of global plus US specific air quality data; showcasing BigQuery functionality and demonstrating well-crafted narration.

title: 2nd place solution
review: One of the top solutions of the recently concluded multi-modal [Shopee competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/shopee-product-matching) (text + image). Uses LightGBM and Graph Attention Networks meta models.

title: Moneyball
review: A classic Notebook inspired by the famously revolutionary [Moneyball](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moneyball) approach to baseball. Engaging narration and clean code make the data and insights accessible.

title: Airbnb data analysis
review: An extensive exploration of NYC Airbnb data which features well-designed, interactive map visuals, detailed interpretations, and a concise summary section.

title: Model Cards
review: The final entry in Kaggle's new [Intro to AI Ethics course](https://www.kaggle.com/learn/intro-to-ai-ethics) discusses the concept of [Model Cards](https://arxiv.org/abs/1810.03993) which aim to promote informed usage of models via increased transparency and documentation.

title: Predicting Survival on the Titanic with RF, LR, NB
review: This work takes us back to basics with a well narrated EDA plus several baseline models for the [Titanic starter competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/titanic). Note the clean visuals and detailed documentation.

title: (SHOPEE) Embedding Visualizations before/after INB
review: This notebook illustrates the technique of iterative neighbourhood blending, a cluster optimisation method developed for the [1st place solution](https://www.kaggle.com/c/shopee-product-matching/discussion/238136) in the recent Shopee competition.

title: Do Left Handed Pitchers Make More Money?
review: We continue our baseball theme from last week with an intriguing question and its data-based answer. Note the engaging narration and the thoughtful conclusions.

title: Industrial Accident Causal Analysis
review: An exploratory work that is exceptionally well organised, and features clean & powerful (bokeh) visuals. Intermediate insights are highlighted via green boxes, and the conclusions section is exemplary.

title: What's Cooking?
review: This well-structured work explored a [food recipes dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/c/whats-cooking-kernels-only) and built a baseline model; all with engaging narration and interpretations. The impressive debut Notebook of a current Kernels Grandmaster.

title: bms-baseline
review: A part of the [3rd place solution](https://www.kaggle.com/c/bms-molecular-translation/discussion/243932) for the recently concluded molecular translation competition, this Notebook showcases a transformer framework that uses TPU for significant speed boost.

title: Swinformer + CutMix + AMP + Accelerate + W&B
review: Showcases a vision transformer with huggingface accelerate and Weights & Biases performance tracking. The extensive notebook also features various other custom tools and methods.

title: Getting started with {tidymodels} and xgboost
review: A well explained intro to leveraging the power of XGBoost using the highly modular R tidymodels framework. Features the new usemodels package, and includes references for further study.

title: Data Science in the Cloud: Who wins the cloud war?
review: This work provides a comparison of the big three cloud providers in terms of their usage within the (Kaggle) data science community. External and custom graphics enrich the narrative.

title: Don't Be Left Behind: Data Science Literacy
review: A well narrated look at the state of data science in the [2020 Kaggle Survey](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2020). Note how plots are accompanied by a relatively objective description plus a more subjective interpretation of their implications.

title: CaseStudy - EDA for Cardio Good Fitness
review: This detailed exploration goes the extra mile to understand a small dataset of treadmill sales with user demographics. Featuring consistent interpretations of charts and tables.

title: LEGO Minifigures - PyTorch and Neptune.ai Template
review: A masterfully built end-to-end pytorch model for Lego figures. The code is clean and well organised. Note the logging via neptune.ai, as well as the error analysis at the end.

title: Airfoil Noise Prediction Modeling using GPR
review: An in-depth exploratory analysis and model building for an airflow dataset. Features well-designed plot grid layouts as well as detailed narration and interpretation of the findings.

title: RFCX & FastAI: Trick to Load Spectrogram Fast
review: A clean and well-documented tutorial to preprocessing audio data into spectrogram images with FastAI. With audio competitions becoming more frequent, this is a great starting point for experimentation.

title: See the flow of bikes
review: This work present a visual analysis of bike sharing flow from a city of Toronto dataset; complete with clusters, maps, and network graphs that showcase the bike movement.

title: A closer look at the FIFA Ranking
review: Another classic Notebook by Jonathan that showcases the tailored exploration of a dataset in great detail with detailed explanations, beautiful graphs, and insightful interpretation.

title: Holocene Volcanic Eruptions: Data Exploration
review: A well-designed analysis of [volcano activity](https://www.kaggle.com/smithsonian/volcanic-eruptions) that features a clear structure, clean code, and a set of great interactive visuals.

title: Loan Classification || Detecting Credit Defaults
review: This somewhat unfinished work presents a detailed exploration of credit default risk data. Note the thoughtful introduction and explanations, as well as the well-designed plot grid layouts.

title: Brain failure prediction
review: An extensive starter-level work that walks through and carefully documents the steps of encountering a new dataset, data wrangling, visualisation, and model building.

title: Visualizing Terrorist Attacks on India
review: A visual analysis of terrorism in India in a global context. This work makes an interesting use of grid plots to contrast the various features and facets of the grim dataset.

title: Popular Kagglers on the Datasets Analysis
review: This work is interesting not just for the different angles of analysis, but also as a historical document on how much our community's engagement with datasets has evolved, and who the early adopters were.

title: Is A Vaccinated Country a Happy One? Data Analysis
review: This work combines two interesting data sets: it presents a narrated exploration of country-level Covid-19 vaccination progress in the context of happiness indicators.

title: Wind Power Forecasting using TensorFlow
review: A well-structured learner project on forecasting with deep learning architectures. The wrangling and modelling steps are clean and have detailed documentation.

title: Ad-Clicks EDA & Classification
review: A compact exploration and logistic regression model for ad clicks. This work is centered around well-designed interactive visuals and uses a consistent colour scheme.

title: Recipes tf-idf and Bigrams
review: This work showcases the power of combining well-designed visuals with detailed context information that sets the stage for the results to be interpreted.

title: WHR 2021- EDA and Linear Regression- beginner
review: An extensive exploratory analysis of [World Happiness data](https://www.kaggle.com/ajaypalsinghlo/world-happiness-report-2021) in Portuguese; featuring summary visuals, a baseline model, and a comparison of Brasil vs Portugal.

title: BERT + TPUs + JAX + HuggingFace
review: A great tutorial Notebook for getting started with multiple powerful tools in an NLP readability challenge. Note the comprehensive explanations of code and concepts.

title: Introduction to Volcanology, Seismograms and LGBM
review: A well-narrated journey into the context and challenges of forecasting volcano eruptions. Note the use of external images to illustrate and enrich the Notebook.

title: Does Money Buy Happiness?
review: The perennial question is being investigated with statistical and dataviz tools, with particular attention to model residuals and interaction effects.

title: Fraud Detection - SMOTE, XGBoost & Business Impact
review: A detailed analysis of credit card fraud data using a synthetic oversampling approach for the imbalanced classification problem. Also note the discussion on precision-recall vs ROC metrics.

title: Analyzing Editors Descriptions | Hidden Gems
review: Time to get meta: This work explores the Hidden Gems series, specifically the text and sentiment of my reviews, with great ideas, narration, and structure. And now it contains itself.

title: Evolution of social complexity: A data analysis
review: This Notebook studies the changes in social complexity over time. It applies external diagrams to great effect, and features detailed interpretations of its findings.

title: Tweet Sentiment Extraction Pytorch
review: A well-described intro to sentiment classification with RoBERTa and huggingface transformers. Note the detailed explanations on model architecture and preprocessing.

title: Differential Expression Analysis with Bioconductor
review: This work showcases an extensive analysis of gene expression data, and features great narration, informative visuals, and clean code using the popular R bioconductor package.

title: English PL Players' stat: Data-viz with Plotly
review: A visual exploration of Premier League football statistics. The interactivity of the visuals helps break down their complexity; and narration provides the relevant context.

title: Getting staRted in R: Graphing Data
review: A great step-by-step tutorial into dataviz with R and ggplot2. Note, that this Notebook requires you to solve its hands-on exercises for it to run correctly.

title: The Rise of Data Science Interest in India
review: An expertly narrated and structured analysis with tons of great insights, pictograms, visuals, and more. The interpretations are detailed and much exploratory ground is covered.

title: 2ndPlace Solution
review: The Pytorch training notebook for the runner up solution in the recently finished [SETI competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/seti-breakthrough-listen). Custom mixup was one of the main differentiators; see also the related [discussion post](https://www.kaggle.com/c/seti-breakthrough-listen/discussion/266397).

title: We are from our childhood
review: This work investigates survey responses for differences between rural and urban living; featuring clean visuals and thorough comments. Plus a Saint Exupéry quote; what more does one need?

title: Computer vision with seedlings
review: An exceptionally well narrated Notebook on image classification, which features a custom segmentation strategy for preprocessing as well as detailed interpretations and documentation.

title: Hourly Energy Consumption: Time Series Analysis
review: This work presents a collection of time series analysis methods which include some pretty cool and powerful (interactive) visuals to explore different aspects of the data.

title: Magic #2 - An Explanation
review: Breaking down winning solutions is always a great way to learn. This work explains and implements one of the two key 'magic' ingredients shared by the 1st place team in the recent [SETI competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/seti-breakthrough-listen/discussion/266385).

title: Energy in the Netherlands, an introductory kernel
review: An extensive work on data wrangling and exploration for an electricity consumption dataset. Note the detailed comments and interpretations that accompany each step.

title: A gentle introduction to wavelet for data analysis
review: A comprehensive guide to wavelets and their applications by the author of the Python [scaleogram package](https://github.com/alsauve/scaleogram). Featuring exemplary explanations and powerful visuals.

title: Default of Credit Card - EDA & Catboost w/Ft.Eng
review: This Notebook presents a detailed analysis and modelling of credit card default payments. The consistent narration and clean facet plot layouts are among the highlights of this work.

title: Starting point: Big Query and London Crime
review: A narrated introduction to Google's Big Query powering the exploration of a crime dataset. The tools and SQL are well explained; and beyond that the visuals help to understand the quirks of the dataset.

title: Deep Sea Dive into Top 10% - Survival Guide
review: The famous Titanic starter challenge is always worth a look for creative content, such as this well illustrated and narrated end-to-end analysis featuring helpful infographics and references.

title: Cropland Mapping - Random Forest & Neural Network
review: Written in an engaging style, this work compares tree-based and deep learning methods for a tabular multiclass problem and discusses preprocessing; specifically highly correlated features.

title: Neighbourhood Equity and Toronto Bike Share
review: A thorough exploration of bike sharing accessibility and social factors. This work makes great use of geospatial maps and features expertly structured narration, complete with references.

title: What's on the Menu EDA
review: An analysis of historical menus and dishes, which addresses the related challenges in data cleaning and aggregation. The inclusion of actual menu scans helps a lot in understanding the data.

title: Classification: How imbalanced is 'imbalanced'?
review: A neat Notebook illustrating the issue of imbalance in classification problems alongside resampling approaches to address it. Note the well-designed overview plot and literature suggestions.

title: BGG Ratings, Mechanics & Miniatures?!
review: This work presents a well-narrated exploration of a [board game dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/mrpantherson/board-game-data). Detailed interpretations of visuals and tables are always helpful for a reader, and provide the flow that every good EDA needs.

title: fastai multi-core TPU Pets Sample
review: A technical Notebook that demonstrates a Python implementation to run FastAI model on TPUs, via Pytorch XLA. Brief and efficient. Check out the corresponding [github package](https://github.com/butchland/fastai_xla_extensions).

title: MLB_final_1
review: The winning solution of the recent MLB Engagement challenge is accompanied by a [discussion post](https://www.kaggle.com/c/mlb-player-digital-engagement-forecasting/discussion/274255) describing the GRU network and its preprocessing layers.

title: TF/JAX Tutorials - Part1
review: This well-narrated intro notebook kicks off a series of tutorials for TensorFlow and JAX; the latter of which is rapidly gaining popularity. Great for getting started with the basics.

title: [1d-CNN] DenseNet1d
review: This Pytorch implementation of a one-dimensional CNN by the [2nd place finisher of the recent G2Net competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/g2net-gravitational-wave-detection/discussion/275341) demonstrates the kind of models that provided an edge in that challenge.

title: Earthquakes in Greece (exploratory analysis)
review: A visual exploration of a century of earthquakes recorded in the current territory of Greece. Features multiple well-designed interactive maps, and annotates its code and findings throughout.

title: Music Generation: LSTM
review: Exceptionally well structured and narrated, this musical experimentation learns from Chopin to write its own piano melodies using LSTMs. Note the stylish gifs and playable audio files.

title: Mapping poverty around the world
review: A geospatial exploration of poverty indices and the metrics that contribute to them. The well-designed folium maps gradually increase in information to paint a comprehensive picture.

title: 2017 German Elections : some results
review: A somewhat topical entry, this notebook produces expert visuals to analyse the previous German voting patterns in 2017. Lots of inspiration to study and compare the recent 2021 election.

title: How popular is Kaggle in Africa?
review: The [2021 Kaggle Survey](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021) is out, and this work showcases the steadily rising numbers of Kagglers from Africa and studies their demographics and experience in a global context.

title: Logbook Analysis and Weather Prediction
review: This exploration of 18th century ocean ship logbooks features detailed narration, insightful map visuals, well-documented custom functions, and another blast from the past: Theano.

title: A Look at Sentiment on the Kaggle Forums
review: An in-depth analysis of positive vs negative sentiment in posts and interactions throughout our community forums and Notebooks. Lots of interesting angles and insights into this meta data.

title: Be on the radar: visualization of job profiles
review: A delightfully styled and cleanly structured exploration of professional profiles in last year's Kaggle survey. Note the detailed interpretations and the consistent colour scheme.

title: Petfinder Pawpularity EDA & fastai starter
review: A clean and concise FastAI starting point for the recently launched [Pawpularity competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/petfinder-pawpularity-score); complete with the popular Swin Transformer model in a classification approach.

title: The Learning Gap
review: This work explores the learning gap in US public schools as caused by socio-economic inequalities and exacerbated by Covid-19. It features great narration, citations, and visual themes.

title: Data Professional in Small vs Large Companies
review: This work approaches the [2021 Kaggle Survey](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021) from an interesting angle of comparing the Data Scientist experience in smaller vs larger companies. Great intro and narrative flow.

title: arXiv - Taxonomy e Top Influential Papers
review: An exploration of arXiv metadata which showcases the popularity of preprints in different fields alongside their most cited papers. I like the utility functions and the heatmaps for top papers.

title: The 5 Types of Kagglers
review: Using the 2021 Kaggle Survey data, this notebook identifies and studies clusters of participants based on selected features derived from their responses. Note the interpretation and narration.

title: Recreating Gapminder visualisation with Bokeh
review: A step by step guide on how to reproduce the dataviz techniques pioneered by the late, great Hans Rosling using the Python Bokeh library. Clean code and much attention to detail.

title: [#1 Solution] PID Controller Matching (V1)
review: This notebook presents part of the winning solution for the recent [Ventilator Pressure competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/ventilator-pressure-prediction). The key matching algoriths are well explained and illustrated in a detailed way.

title: Top 10 the Most Unique Countries from 2021 Survey
review: A detailed analysis of [Kaggle Survey](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021) data which goes beyond the average Kaggler's profile and studies the rarer respondents characteristics and their countries of residence.

title: Mental Health : Plotly Interactive Viz
review: This work presents a visual exploration of a mental health survey and features an interesting style with animated pictograms, narrative boxes, and a consistent colour scheme throughout.

title: Celebrity Face Swap
review: A fun little Notebook that explains and applies the basic steps to assemble a simple face swapping algorithm. The code is clean and well documented. Results induce only light nightmares.

title: How to get a Promotion 101
review: An exploratory analysis of job promotion data. Note, how the narration guides the reader through the Notebook and its various insights in a well-structured flow.

title: Time Series Anomaly Detection
review: A well documented Notebook that explores outlier detection via isolation forest models on the example of an NYC Taxi Demand dataset. Note the interactive visuals via the bokeh and holoview tools.

title: The 50 shades of happiness in a t-SNE world !
review: This brief work uses World Happiness Report data to craft a creative set of visuals that impose a hex structure onto t-SNE projected maps of countries and their happiness features.

title: The Worsening Gender Pay Gap in Data Science
review: In this Notebook, the author uses beautiful custom visuals alongside extensive interpretations to study gender pay gaps in the [Kaggle Survey data](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021) from various angles.

title: Introduction To Financial Mathematics
review: A well structured and detailed guide to financial concepts and their underlying mathematical tools. Impressively comprehensive and featuring numerous templates of clean code.

title: A Story about Unsupervised Learning
review: An extensive and well written compendium that covers a range of methods for dimensionality reduction and outlier detection. Expertly designed; with great visuals and explanations.

title: [Annoy]Similar Images ver2
review: This work is a great example of image data cleaning and quality checks with the help of the [annoy library](https://github.com/spotify/annoy). It emphasises the importance of understanding your training data.

title: Visualizing Convolution Filters
review: A visual dive into the inner workings of convolution layers and their feature maps. It explains and illustrates neatly how features become more abstract as images pass through multiple layers.

title: Does sunshine or money equal to happiness?
review: I like how the narration draws the reader into the analysis, which follows its own creative approach and hypotheses. Documenting and interpreting your findings proves once again important.

title: Food Nutrition Analysis+EDA
review: This work explores a food dataset along its different categories using different visualisation strategies and clear structure. Note, how narration and interpretations help in communicating the results.

title: Industrial Machine Anomaly Detection
review: This Notebook features a clear structure, well thought-out visuals, and concise conclusions and references sections. It provides a brief EDA before comparing different algorithms for finding anomalies.

title: G-Research: TabNet starter notebook
review: This work assembles a flexible experimentation setup for the ongoing [Crypto Forecasting competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/g-research-crypto-forecasting). The different steps are cleanly separated and well documented; including a custom CV split.

title: How free has the world become so far
review: A well-organised study of freedom and happiness in countries around the world. Consistent narration and interpretation are strong features of this notebook.

title: Disparity in Engagement in Digital Learning
review: A study of student engagement in digital learning and the socio-economic factors that contribute to it. The comprehensive narration is the standout feature of this work.

title: Cyclistic bike-share : Case study
review: This exploratory work showcases strong narrative elements when it comes to explaining, documenting, and interpreting the analysis. Also note how the notebook is structured into clear sections.

title: Data Heroines - Saving the World Through Data
review: A [Kaggle Survey](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021) story with a unique look and style that takes us on a great adventure with the Super Heroines of Data Science. Note, that this is the work of 3 authors.

title: Find where I truly belong
review: A personalised exploration of [Kaggle Survey data](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021) with great structure, visuals, and narration. Focussed on a deep dive into a specific demographic; with criticial examination of the survey questions.

title: Cricket Analytics: Decoding Stories
review: This extensive work provides a thorough exploration of Indian Premier League cricket data; examining prominent players and their trajectories to success as well as overview stats for batsmen and bowlers.

title: Mental Health in Tech
review: A well documented debut Notebook on the complex and important topic of mental health in the (tech) workplace. Detailed narration and interpretation of visuals make the findings accessible.

title: The Success Story: Compete & Win with Kaggle Data
review: An interesting [Kaggle Survey](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021) story, approaching the data from an entrepreneurial angle and trying to extract actionable insights for small businesses. The narrative flow is engaging.

title: Analysis of the show 'Parks and Recreation'
review: This detailed exploration of Parks & Rec episode data takes the reader from data cleaning to visualising character and episode stats. Great narration and introductory outline.

title: Understanding and Improving CycleGANs - Tutorial
review: A well documented guide to image style transfer through generative networks; featuring great illustrations and explanations. Check it out if you always wanted to compare apples to oranges.

title: Starter: AutoTel Shared Car Locations
review: A well-rounded analyis of car sharing usage patterns over time in Tel Aviv. Check out the time series and geospatial visuals as well as the LightGBM baseline predicting neighbourhood availability.

title: Egyptian Endeavour - Moment of Truth
review: This [Kaggle Survey](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021) analysis focusses on the growing number of Egyptian Kagglers and their characteristics. Note the consistent colour scheme and style, as well as the story-telling flow.

title: Avocado | EDA
review: A slightly unfinished exploration of avocado prices over time, which nonetheless displays well organised visuals and interpretations. Note the statistical view of distributions and their outliers.

title: Let's Respect the Veterans
review: An extensive [Kaggle Survey](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021) deep dive that compares Kagglers with <= 1 year experience to those who have been coding for 2 decades or more. Strong narration, interpretations, and visuals.

title: team-merged ensemble FixedNewModelsExp029nonmean
review: The 2nd-place winners of the recent Pawpularity competition published their final ensemble code, and I would like to encourage other winning teams to do the same. Also check out the [related write-up](https://www.kaggle.com/c/petfinder-pawpularity-score/discussion/300929).

title: A journey through the history of soccer
review: A detailed exploration of global football data; from data cleaning to historical overview stats to performance metrics. All insights come with clean visuals and thorough interpretation.

title: How to Create Award Winning Data Visualizations
review: A step-by-step guide providing a blueprint for building sophisticated data visuals. The thought process is explained with care and attention to detail, and the outcome is stunning.

title: Bellabeat Capstone Project in R
review: This notebook presents a well-structured study of fitness tracker data with carefully designed visuals, detailed interpretations, and thoughtful discussions and recommendations sections.

title: Analysing Indian Recipes
review: A tasty exploration of ingredients, characteristics, and preparations of Indian cuisine. The analysis is accessible, flows well, and includes a number of pictures to whet your appetite.

title: Pakistan's Rising Data Science 2021
review: A detailed exploration of Data Science in Pakistan and the characteristics of the predominantly young respondents based on [Kaggle Survey data](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021). Love the intro, references, and points to note.

title: KFC vs Mc Donalds Vs Cafe Coffee Day
review: Get your morning coffee (and snacks!) in Bangalore using this compact Notebook, which features a map, summary visuals, and detailed interpretation of the findings.

title: Imagenet embeddings+RAPIDS SVR+Finetuned models
review: The winning strategy in the recent [Pawpularity competition](https://www.kaggle.com/c/petfinder-pawpularity-score), explained by the legendary Grandmaster himself: a clever framework of pretrained image embeddings and RAPIDS ensembling.

title: Transformers Course - Chapter 2 - TF & Torch
review: Part of a series which brings the fantastic [Huggingface course](https://huggingface.co/course/chapter1/1) into Kaggle. The Huggingface content is well presented, and the Notebook shows both the Tensorflow and Pytorch code.

title: Exploring Data Analytics in Africa
review: A great looking [Kaggle Survey](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021) analysis of the state of data science & ML in Africa. The visuals are clean and focussed, and the related insights are highlighted.

title: Data analysis of Rio de Janeiro olympics 2016
review: This work is a visual exploration of Olympic athletes and their characteristics. It features a variety of different plotting styles and provides interpretation for the aspects it studies.

title: notebook9298460840
review: This is the inference Notebook for the winning solution in the recent Jigsaw Toxic Severity competition by one of the world's top Kagglers. Check out the [training code here](https://github.com/GuanshuoXu/Jigsaw-Rate-Severity-of-Toxic-Comments).

title: Kaggle Story: B.C. (before covid) and through
review: A well documented [Kaggle Survey](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021) exploration that showcases a range of different overview visuals and tables. The focus is on the last 3 years: pre-Covid and during Covid.

title: Fitness Tracker: A Usage Trends Analysis With R
review: A beautifully illustrated and extensively narrated study of fitness tracker data. Note the clear structure and the emphasis on often neglected aspects like data cleaning and discussion & recommendations.

title: Kannada MNIST: Choosing the Right Optimizer
review: A detailed and well-structured overview of popular deep learning optimisers, from SGD to Nadam. The maths are supplemented with tensorflow/keras implementation comparisons.

title: EDA and Data Storytelling on Disney Movies
review: This work is a compact exploration of Disney movies and franchises over the years. The static and interactive visuals share a consistent style and are accompanied by interpretation.

title: Rain in Australia with EDA & H2O (88.4% AUC)
review: An extensive analysis of Australian rainfall with many interesting visuals, in particular the time series and correlations, and detailed modelling with various H2O estimators.

title: Explore ML&DS survey 2021 | Ukraine
review: A well illustrated [Kaggle Survey](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021) analysis of data scientists and machine learning practioners in Ukraine. The narrative flow is centered around different types of exploratory visuals.

title: Capstone - Case Study Bellabeat
review: A beautifully structured and extensively documented exploration of fitness tracker data. This work showcases detailed interpretations of findings and concludes with actionable insights.

title: Learning in Cyberspace: a Story of Pandemic Times
review: A comprehensive study of online learning during Covid-19, featuring carefully designed visuals, extensive interpretations, and multiple related datasets for context and augmentation.

title: Big Macs & Rock Stars: What Seperates Top Earners
review: Employing well designed visuals and engaging narration to study [Kaggle Survey data](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021) in the light of global income distributions. Check out the detailed interpretations and conclusions.

title: yolo_ensemle
review: The înference notebook for the 2nd place solution in the recent Great Barrier Reef competition. Also check out the associated [write-up post](https://www.kaggle.com/c/tensorflow-great-barrier-reef/discussion/307760) with more training and postprocessing details.

title: Football Transfers 2000-2018
review: An EDA notebook that studies the performance of football clubs in the transfer market. Summary visuals of different rankings provide a comprehensive exploration from different angles.

title: Opioids in the US: Initial Graphs
review: A well explained and illustrated starter Notebook for a dataset which records the evolution of the opioid epidemic in the United States; an ongoing crisis with devastating societal impact.

title: What's in a Name? [2021 Kaggle Survey Competition]
review: This [Kaggle Survey](https://www.kaggle.com/c/kaggle-survey-2021) analysis presents a thoughtful examination of what the field of data science entails. Note in particular the detailed introduction and reference section.

title: 2xYOLOv5l6 + tracking [LB 0.678/ Private 0.722]
review: The 10th place solution of the recent Great Barrier Reef detection competition features some interesting computer vision tricks. Make sure to read also the [corresponding discussion post]( https://www.kaggle.com/c/tensorflow-great-barrier-reef/discussion/307756).

title: Bike Sharing in Boston VS COVID19
review: A visual study of the impact of Covid-19 on bike sharing habits, demonstrating the narrative element of insights boxes to highlight findings. Also see the data cleaning notes.

title: feedback-nn-train
review: The Longformer training Notebook from the winning solution of the recently finished NLP competition on evaluating student writing. Check out the [write-up on the multi-stage approach](https://www.kaggle.com/c/feedback-prize-2021/discussion/313177).

title: Data Science with Compassion
review: An extensive exploratory and modelling analysis of country characteristics relevant to micro-funding strategies. Note the presentation style that establishes a dialog with the data.

title: US elections study with enriched data + estimation
review: An exploration and modelling notebook on US election data; augmented with several demographic features. Check out the thorough documentation and the diverse set of visualisations.

title: Patterns of colorectal cancer - image clustering
review: A clustering analysis with great visuals and detailed interpretations that explore a medical dataset. Note how the clean narrative structure makes the approach and results accessible.

title: COVID-19 Study with Epidemiology models
review: This work presents a comprehensive study of Covid-19 progressions from the early days of the pandemic. Featuring well illustrated implementations of epidemiological models.

title: NBA player of the week ... he's on fire !!!
review: A detailed exploration of a basketball award category and the characteristics of winning players and teams. Check out the strong narration, the clean data wrangling, and the fantastic visuals.

title: Exploring Global Inequality and Growth
review: This work analyses the global inequalities in wealth, and their evolution over time, through sets of comparison visualisations and clearly documents the insights derived from those.

title: Capstone: Bellabeat Case Study | R
review: An in-depth investigation of fitness tracker data that showcases great structure and interesting visuals. Note the final section that aims to derive actionable recommendations.
